compressed archieve how i make
Got it — you want to compress your Power BI file (.pbix) into an archive format (like .zip or .rar). That’s straightforward, and here’s how you can do it:

🗂 How to Make a Compressed Archive of Your Power BI File
Locate Your File

Find your .pbix file in File Explorer.

Right-Click → Send to Compressed Folder

Right-click the file.

Choose Send to → Compressed (zipped) folder.

This will create a .zip file in the same location with the same name.

Optional: Use Third-Party Tools

If you prefer .rar or more advanced compression:

Install WinRAR or 7-Zip.

Right-click the file → Add to archive….

Choose .zip or .rar and set compression level (Normal, Maximum).

Rename & Organize

Rename the archive to something clear, e.g., MINIPROJECT_EXCEL_POWERBI.zip.

You can also add multiple files (Excel + PBIX + documentation) into one archive.

⚡ Why Compress?
Makes it easier to share via email or GitHub.

Reduces file size for faster upload/download.

Keeps related files bundled together.

