how to view zip file if i upload
When you upload a ZIP file, you’re basically packaging your .pbix (and maybe other files) into a compressed folder. To view what’s inside the ZIP, here’s what you do:

🖥️ On Windows
Locate the uploaded ZIP file (e.g., in File Explorer or your cloud storage).

Double-click the ZIP file → it opens like a normal folder.

You’ll see the contents (your .pbix, Excel, Word docs, etc.).

To extract:

Right-click the ZIP → Extract All…

Choose a destination folder → click Extract.

Now you can open the .pbix in Power BI Desktop or other files in their respective apps.

📱 On Mobile
Most phones have built-in ZIP support:

Tap the ZIP → it shows contents.

Use “Extract” or “Unzip” option to open files.

🌐 If Uploaded Online (e.g., GitHub, OneDrive, Google Drive)
GitHub: The ZIP will appear as a downloadable file. People download and then unzip locally.

OneDrive/Google Drive: You can preview some contents, but usually you’ll need to download and unzip to fully view/open the .pbix.

⚡ Tip: If your goal is to share your Power BI project with others, uploading the .pbix directly is often better. Use ZIP only if you’re bundling multiple files (PBIX + Excel + documentation).

