this is my ip file why its make mistakes
I see what happened — the error message “No files to extract” means your ZIP archive (my mini.zip) was created but it’s actually empty inside. That’s why WinRAR can’t find anything to unpack.

Here’s why this usually happens and how to fix it:

🔍 Why Your ZIP Shows Empty
File wasn’t added properly: When you made the archive, the .pbix or other files weren’t included — you zipped an empty folder instead.

Wrong drag‑and‑drop: If you dragged the folder icon but didn’t select the contents, the archive may have been created with no files.

Corrupted archive: Rare, but sometimes compression fails and produces a blank ZIP.

🛠 How to Fix It
Check the folder

Open the folder my mini on your desktop.

Make sure your .pbix file (and any other files you want) are inside.

Re‑create the ZIP

Right‑click the folder → Send to → Compressed (zipped) folder.

This will generate a new ZIP with the contents included.

Verify before sharing

Double‑click the new ZIP.

You should see your .pbix file listed inside.

If you see the files, extraction will work fine.

Optional: Use WinRAR/7‑Zip

Right‑click the folder → Add to archive….

Choose .zip or .rar.

Confirm the file list shows your .pbix before clicking OK.

⚡ Quick tip: Always zip the folder containing your files, not just an empty placeholder. That way, when you upload, others can open the archive and see your Power BI project inside.

