When you upload a ZIP file to Google Drive (or OneDrive), you won’t be able to open the .pbix directly inside the cloud — Drive treats it as just a compressed package. Here’s how you can view it:

📂 Viewing a ZIP File in Google Drive
Upload the ZIP to your Drive.

Double‑click the ZIP in Drive:

Drive will show a preview of the contents (list of files inside).

You can browse but not open .pbix directly.

Download the ZIP:

Right‑click → Download.

Save it to your computer.

Extract the ZIP locally:

Right‑click the downloaded ZIP → Extract All… (Windows built‑in) or use WinRAR/7‑Zip.

Now you’ll see your .pbix file inside.

🖥️ Opening the Power BI File
Once extracted, double‑click the .pbix file.

It will open in Power BI Desktop (make sure you have it installed).

From there, you can view and edit your dashboards.

⚡ Key Point: Google Drive (and similar cloud storage) only lets you store and preview ZIP contents. To actually use your Power BI file, you must download and unzip it first.

